  + [purpose] is prevent local branch completion from becoming global idle while reviewable work and valuable periphery remain
  + [not_purpose] is endless repetition of a completed branch, proof pursuit, hidden daemon work, automatic commits, or undisciplined association chasing
  + [proof_status] is operating_cadence_correction_not_math_evidence

& [WalkingCadence] is the corrected operating loop
  + [step_001_settle_completed_step] is use StepBalanceWalk to name completed action, balance, settlement, and next candidate
  + [step_002_bind_work_frame] is use commit, ref, or WORKTREE bookends to identify what changed
  + [step_003_review] is use RepoFirstInternalScan, TurnBookmark, or TrailingChecksumVoice when the frame needs reflection
  + [step_004_scan_periphery] is identify hot zones, warmth zones, boundary issues, identity uncertainty, missed work, and new potential
  + [step_005_check_pursuit_value] is require boundary, identity, evidence, whole-field, governance, contradiction, or truth/security value before active pursuit
  + [step_006_plan_next_step] is select a bounded next object or preserve outside
  + [step_007_follow_through] is continue with source/spec before new analysis or implementation when a next object is selected
  + [step_008_return_to_walk] is return to StepBalanceWalk when run continuity breaks or proof/security gates require checkpointing

  = must: treat branch pause as local to the branch, not as global cessation of RH workspace walking
  = must: continue while a reviewed work frame exposes valuable periphery and balance remains stable enough
  = must: use WORKTREE as the bookend when no commit exists yet, without pretending a commit happened
  = must: preserve source before specification before analysis or implementation
  = must: keep special-prime, Lambda overlay, explicit residual, Euler/log-derivative, and zeta-reference branches subordinate to whole-field RH objects
  = must: keep proof, disproof, zero certification, and critical-line authority outside finite exploratory traces
  = should: let completed branch conclusions become route maps for the next review or periphery scan
  = should: favor one bounded governed slice per wakeup or turn rather than unbounded grid expansion
  - never: delete or pause a continuation schedule merely because one local branch has reached a useful conclusion
  - never: reopen a paused branch by density, more labels, more windows, or proof-facing scans without a new source-defined purpose
  - never: treat motion itself as evidence of truth

& [WalkingContinuityCorrectionSJS] is the specification justification trace
  + [processed_stage_set] is source_preserved, delineated, canonicalized, constraint_checked, justified, and cadence_scoped
  + [processing_result] is accepted_operating_cadence_correction
  + [reasoning_result] is SOP walking already requires step settlement, balance, next-step selection, repo-first review, delayed checksum review, and pursuit-value gates, so local branch completion should trigger review and next-lead routing instead of global idle

(walking_continuity_correction) :operating cadence: /settle, review, scan, plan, follow through/ |proof claims|
  + [inside] is walking continuity over work frames with pursuit-value gates
  + [boundary] is local branch closure may pause that branch but must route remaining valuable periphery
  |outside| proof, disproof, zero certification, automatic commits, hidden daemon work, and chasing every association
